content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 15 ยง 35.9 - Compliance

State Regulations
(a) Compliance
shall consist of: (1)
surrender of
registration and license plate(s); or
(2)
expiration of the registration; or
(3)
payment of a civil penalty
as provided in section
35.3
(k) of this

Part. (b) Place. Compliance, other than by surrender of registration to
another state, can only be made to an issuing office or the central office of
this department. (c) Receipt for compliance. Except where compliance is accomplished by expiration of
the registration, the person making compliance shall be given a receipt
indicating the type and date of compliance. Notes
